When a user attempts to tick a task checkbox on a page they don't have permissions to edit, Confluence will display a warning:
{quote}Oops! You can't update this task because you are not allowed to edit the page it appears on.{quote}

In German the displayed message is:
{quote}Hoppla! Sie können diese Aufgabe nicht aktualisieren, weil sie die Seite nicht bearbeiten dürfen, auf der sie angezeigt wird.{quote}

It should be: _Sie können diese Aufgabe nicht aktualisieren, weil Sie die Seite nicht bearbeiten dürfen_ - the first 'sie' should be capitalised. At the moment, this is a grammar mistake - the lowercase 'sie' doesn't refer to the user.

I got an email titled "[Confluence] Recommended in Brigade Confluence for Joe Lencioni - Apr 09, 2015" and it had some error output in it:

{quote}Error: RuntimeException occurred while performing an XHTML storage transformation (In template Confluence.Templates.User.userLinkUrl: When evaluating "contextPath()": Error while computing function "contextPath()": null){quote}

This appeared in the "Most Popular" section. No idea how to reproduce.

